A fallen mast pole near Muizenberg station has disrupted train services between Retreat and Simonâ€™s Town. CAPE TOWN - Metrorail in the Western Cape says a bus service is currently operating between Retreat and Simon's Town stations after train services were cancelled when a mast pole blew over near Muizenberg station this morning and fell on an overhead wire.  Metrorail's Riana Scott says: "One of our mast poles blew over at Muizenberg. Our technicians are on site busy repairing. Fortunately it's off peak and at the moment there's a bus shuttle between Retreat and Simon's Town until they've managed to fix that."  